==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Male
<hw>Male</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>m⟦acir⟧le</ets>, OF.
<ets>masle</ets>, <ets>mascle</ets>, fr. L. <ets>masculus</ets> male,
masculine, dim. of <ets>mas</ets> a male; possibly akin to E.
<ets>man</ets>. Cf. <er>Masculine</er>, <er>Marry</er>, <pos>v.
t.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of or pertaining to the sex that begets
or procreates young, or (in a wider sense) to the sex that produces
spermatozoa, by which the ova are fertilized; not female; <as>as,
<ex>male</ex> organs</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Capable of producing
fertilization, but not of bearing fruit; -- said of stamens and
antheridia, and of the plants, or parts of plants, which bear
them.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Suitable to the male sex; characteristic or
suggestive of a male; masculine; <as>as, <ex>male</ex>
courage</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Consisting of males; <as>as, a <ex>male</ex>
choir</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <fld>(Mech.)</fld> <def>Adapted for entering another
corresponding piece (the <xex>female</xex> piece) which is hollow and
which it fits; <as>as, a <ex>male</ex> gauge, for gauging the size or
shape of a hole; a <ex>male</ex> screw, etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Male fern</b></col> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>a fern of the
genus <gen>Aspidium</gen> (<spn>Aspidium Filixmas</spn>), used in
medicine as an anthelmintic, esp. against the tapeworm. <spn>Aspidium
marginale</spn> in America, and <spn>Aspidium athamanticum</spn> in
South Africa, are used as good substitutes for the male fern in medical
practice. See <cref>Female fern</cref>, under <er>Female</er>.</cd> --
<col><b>Male rhyme</b></col>, <cd>a rhyme in which only the last
syllables agree, as <xex>laid</xex>, <xex>afraid</xex>,
<xex>dismayed</xex>. See <cref>Female rhyme</cref>, under
<er>Female</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Male screw</b></col>
<fld>(Mech.)</fld>, <cd>a screw having threads upon its exterior which
enter the grooves upon the inside of a corresponding nut or female
screw.</cd> -- <col><b>Male thread</b></col>, <cd>the thread of a male
screw.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Male</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 5 ====
HEADWORD: Male
<hw>Male</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An animal of the male
sex.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A plant bearing only staminate
flowers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Maleadministration</ent>⟦br⟧
